=== cmd 0: [registry sync --help] ===
Sync safe/governor transaction state from on-chain services

Update deployment registry with latest on-chain information. Checks
pending Safe transactions and updates their execution status.

Usage: treb registry sync [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --network <NETWORK>
          Network name or chain ID

      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

      --non-interactive
          Skip interactive prompts (also enabled via TREB_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, CI=true, or non-TTY
          stdin/stdout)

      --tx-hash <HASH>
          Sync a specific transaction hash (fetches receipt, detects proxy upgrades and new
          deployments)

      --rpc-url <RPC_URL>
          Explicit RPC URL (overrides network, required with --tx-hash unless fork is active)

      --clean
          Remove invalid entries while syncing

      --debug
          Print raw API responses to stderr

      --json
          Output as JSON

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
